17
18 WHEREAS, James Richard Hendrix, a native of Lepanto, Arkansas, was a
19 World War II veteran and recipient of the Medal of Honor, the highest
20 military decoration given by the United States Armed Forces, for his actions
21 during that war; and
22
23 WHEREAS, James Hendrix was born on August 20, 1925, and as the son of a
24 sharecropper, he left school at an early age to work alongside his parents on
25 the family farm; and
26
27 WHEREAS, in 1943, at age eighteen (18), James Hendrix was drafted into
28 the United States Army and was sent to Europe, assigned to the 53rd Armored
29 Infantry Battalion, Fourth Armored Division; and
30
31 WHEREAS, after the initial invasion of Normandy by the Allied Forces,
32 James Hendrix and his unit began the march across France to Belgium as part
33 of General George S. Patton's Third Army; and
34
35 WHEREAS, James Hendrix was nineteen (19) years old on December 26,
36 1944, near Assenois, Belgium, when he showed incredibly bravery in helping to
